One of my favorite parts of my job is getting to build a relationship with my clients. It was always hard for me to say goodbye after 12 hrs bonding with a patient and wondering what ever happened to them. Now, I feel like I can give the type of care that I always wanted to but never felt I had the time for at the bedside and I get to see couples transform from scared to confident! We are taught in nursing school to think about the whole person: mental, physical, emotional, spiritual. By being a consistent source of knowledge, experience, empathy, and by actually trying to listen to understand I feel like I'm really getting to be a nurse to my clients! Plus, we have a lot of fun! . ¬∑

Missing this clan today!! I actually wonder a lot about what life would be like with family that lives close by. I moved here to LA at 18, pre-wifi and WhatsApp days. My parents and sister were in Ecuador. Since then, we've added @joshzook93 to the fam, my parents moved back to the States to MN and my sister and Josh moved back to Ecuador to serve vulnerable women. I'm SO grateful for my upbringing and international experience. I'm grateful I don't have to split my travels between more than two places to see my immediate family... But, there are times that I wish we could all be neighbors, popping in for dinner or going on a quick hike together. What is that life like?! Maybe someday... But till then I'll just keep being grateful for the moments where we do get moments all together, and for FaceTime/cell phones. ¬∑

rest /rest/ verb
cease work or movement in order to relax, refresh oneself, or recover strength.

I am very proud to announce that I did no work (not even an Instagram post) for the last week and boy did it feel amazing. Ever since starting my business almost 2 yrs ago (whaaaaatttttt) I haven't stopped. Even if it was just in my brain's never ending to do list or emails or social media, I can't remember ever just turning it off... Except for this last week! I legit laid on my bed overlooking the ocean and stared listening to @hermusicofficial for like an HR. #luxuries ü§£ We pride ourselves in North American culture on being busy. I want to work SO hard, but I also want to know how to rest. Ready (or not) I'm back to reality, turning it back on full throttle and finding some good rhythms to try to keep me balanced.
